articles.headline: Heliot Ramos drives in four runs as Giants rally to beat Red Sox 9-5
articles.description: — Heliot Ramos doubled home two runs to highlight San Francisco's decisive seventh inning after an earlier two-run single, and the Giants rallied to beat the Boston Red Sox 9-5 on Sunday.

articles.headline: Chisholm rallies Yankees to 4-2 win as New York takes 2 of 3 from Orioles
articles.description: — Jazz Chisholm Jr. hit a go-ahead, two-run double off the right-center field wall in a three-run eighth inning, leading the New York Yankees over the Baltimore Orioles 4-2 Sunday.

articles.headline: Yankees' Jazz Chisholm Jr. crosses plate without both shoes
articles.description: A century after Shoeless Joe, both of Jazz Chisholm Jr.'s cleats flew off his feet as he scored from second base in the Yankees' 4-2 win over the Orioles in an unusual morning start Sunday.
